According to expressio unius est exclusionis, the fact that fire, flood, earthquake, and hurricane are listed but not tornado suggests an intent to exclude tornado damage. Therefore, the buyer would likely argue that the clause does not excuse performance due to a tornado.
If the seller tries to include "including but not limited to" in the list of events, ejusdem generis might apply, meaning only natural disasters like those explicitly listed (fire, flood, earthquake, hurricane) would be excused. In this case, a strike is likely not considered a similar event and thus would also not excuse performance.
