#### Contra Proferentem Rule
This rule of interpretation is commonly used by courts to resolve disputes, particularly when dealing with contracts drafted by large entities like banks and insurance companies. The rule essentially means "against the one who offered it," implying that any ambiguity in a contract should be construed against the party that drafted it.
:p What does the contra proferentem rule entail?
??x
The contra proferentem rule states that any ambiguities in a contract should be interpreted in favor of the party that did not draft the contract. This is often used to protect smaller parties from overly complex or one-sided contracts crafted by larger, more powerful entities.
```java
// Example scenario
